    "description": "We at Baxter India International Enterprises are looking for an experienced Consultant Physician based out of Gwalior. If you are a result-oriented professional with a passion for excellence, we want to hear from you.\n\nAbout Baxter India International Enterprises:\nBaxter India International Enterprises is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Educate patients and families on health management and disease prevention\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n• Maintain sterile environments and follow infection control protocols\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Monitor patient progress and adjust treatment plans accordingly\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Post Graduate Diploma in relevant field\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in EMR/EHR\n• Proficiency in BLS/ACLS\n• Proficiency in Infection Control\n• Proficiency in Health Informatics\n• Proficiency in Medical Ethics\n• Proficiency in Diagnostic Skills\n• Proficiency in Medical Coding\n• Proficiency in NABH Standards\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Flexible working hours\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Gwalior, Madhya Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Baxter India International Enterprises!",
